<title>USA: Vimpel-Comms plans secondary offering.</title>
<headline>Vimpel-Comms plans secondary offering.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-04-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Vimpel-Communications said Monday it intends to file with the Securities and Exchange Commission for a secondary offering of American depository shares representing common shares of Vimpel in the U.S. and Canada and outside the U.S. and Canada by FGI Wireless Ltd.</p>
<p>Based on current market prices, the offering is anticipated to be about $100 million, Vimpel said.</p>
<p>FGI is a U.S. company founded in 1993 as an investment vehicle for non-Russian venture capitalists and institutions to invest in Vimpel.</p>
<p>FGI's sole material asset is 3,305,622 shares of Vimpe common.</p>
